            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#VM">
                <p>[...] Myskon, son of Damis son of Kobetos [...] Anthemokritos bade Apellis offer security 
                    [...] said [...] was; he came upon [...] of the Leontines [...] Myskon sitting along the avenue [...] 
                    came (not?) having the money, the price of the cattle; he did not buy [...] went to Empedokles, 
                    son of Mnasimachos [...] let [...] become (liable?) to act as surety (trans. by Miller).</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#VM">
                <p>[...] Myskon, figlio di Damis figlio di Kobetos [...] Anthemokritos ordinò ad Apelis(?) di agire da garante  
                    [...] disse [...] era; si imbatté [...] dei Leontini [...] Myskon seduto lungo il viale [...] 
                    venne (non?) avendo il denaro, il prezzo del bestiame; non comprò [...] andò da Empedokles, 
                    figlio di Mnasimachos [...] lasciò che [...] diventasse garante.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" xml:lang="en">
                <p><!-- (in progress) The text appears on the obverse of an opisthographic lamina with a defixio on the reverse (ISic030019, Arena II(2), no. 45). --></p>
            </div>
